claim.claim-text:
1. A method for controlling an operation of a kimchi storage device that maintains a constant temperature range of a storage chamber by operating a compressor and a heater alternately in a preservation mode of the kimchi storage device, the method comprising the steps of: 
measuring a temperature in the storage chamber; 
determining whether the temperature in the storage chamber is within a temperature range to operate the compressor or within a temperature range to operate the heater; 
if the temperature in the storage chamber is within the temperature range to operate the compressor, then operating the compressor; 
delaying an operation of the heater for a predetermined time when the temperature in the storage chamber is within the temperature range to operate the heater; 
determining, after delay time, whether the temperature in the storage chamber comes within the temperature range to operate the compressor or within the temperature range to operate the heater; 
if the temperature in the storage chamber comes within the temperature range to operate the compressor, then clearing a delay time for operating the heater, and operating the compressor immediately; 
if the temperature in the storage chamber is within a range of temperature to operate the heater, then operating the heater.
